# Cursor Rules — TTS Web App

> **This is the canonical rules file.** Product spec: `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-03-12-tts-web-app-prd.md`. For questions about product, read the PRD. For dev rules, read this file.

## Project Overview
Text-to-speech web app. Users paste text or upload files, select a voice, convert to MP3.

## Task Tracking
- Read `TASKS.md` for the current build checklist
- After completing each task, mark it `[x]` in `TASKS.md`
- Add a one-line summary to `CHANGELOG.md`

## Architecture (2 layers)
1. **Frontend:** React + Tailwind CSS → deployed to Vercel
2. **Backend + GPU:** Python / FastAPI + Chatterbox Multilingual → all on Modal (serverless)

There is NO separate backend service. Modal hosts everything: the API (via `@modal.asgi_app()`), file parsing, chunking, TTS generation, and audio stitching. The stack is just Vercel + Modal.

## Critical Rules

### Modal (Backend API + GPU Worker)
- Serve the FastAPI app using `@modal.asgi_app()` on Modal.
- Use CPU functions for lightweight work: file parsing, chunking, progress tracking, serving files.
- Use GPU functions for heavy work: Chatterbox TTS generation and audio stitching (pydub + ffmpeg).
- Process chunks in parallel batches using Modal's `.map()` or equivalent. Do NOT process sequentially.
- Stitch all audio chunks into a single MP3 on the GPU function. Return only the final MP3.
- Install ffmpeg and pydub in the Modal image.
- Voice reference clips are bundled in the Modal image.
- Use PyMuPDF (`import fitz`) for PDF parsing. Do NOT use PyPDF2.
- Reference: https://modal.com/docs/examples/chatterbox_tts

### Frontend (React)
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling. No other CSS framework.
- Warm & friendly design: soft colors, rounded corners, approachable feel.
- Single page app, no routing needed.
- Voice cards: horizontal row on desktop, vertical stack on mobile.
- Poll backend every 2 seconds for progress during conversion.
- Show "Warming up..." during Modal cold start before progress percentage kicks in.

### Text Processing
- Chunk text at ~300 characters, splitting at sentence boundaries (not mid-word).
- Maximum 20,000 words. Validate on both frontend (word counter) and backend.
- Maximum file upload size: 10 MB.
- Supported file types: .txt, .pdf only.

### Error Handling
- Follow error messages exactly as specified in the PRD error handling table.
- Retry failed chunks up to 3 times silently before showing an error to the user.

### Code Style
- Python: use type hints, async where appropriate, follow PEP 8.
- TypeScript/React: functional components, hooks, no class components.
- Keep files focused — one component per file, one endpoint group per router file.
- No over-engineering. MVP only. Do not add features not in the PRD.

### What NOT to build (excluded from MVP)
- No user authentication or accounts
- No voice cloning / upload your own voice
- No Hebrew language support
- No DOCX file support
- No rate limiting
- No Redis or external persistence
- No payment system
- No Render — there is no separate backend service

